Note: I did change bit-depth and samplerate from the MLP source to get a smaller
filesize (so this release is also for those people who would like to listen to 
Alan Parson's quadrophonic mix of Pink Floyd's Dark Side Of The Moon but don't 
have a fast internet connection). I personally can't make out any difference
between the original MLP 96 kHz / 24 bit source and my downconverted 
44,1 kHz / 16 bit flac files.
These flac files also enable those to play this quadrophonic mix who don't own a DVD-Audio-player.


I strongly encourage anyone to buy the original album on CD / SACD / vinyl!
